				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So how about a compromise between the "Window" camera, and the "see what's ahead of you" camera?
<br />
<br />When you are moving solidly in one direction, the camera goes ahead, so you can see better what's in front of you.  But when you stop or slow down, it ends "see ahead of you mode" and acts more like the "Window" camera.  Maybe with a slow transition so there's less sudden jerkyness.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Here come the fortune cookies!  Here come the fortune cookies!  They're wearing paper hats!</div>
